{
  "texts": [
    "(3) entity resolution, which merges semantically similar entities and relations to reduce noise and shrink the graph.",
    "The three steps are illustrated in Figure 2 and described in detail below.",
    "To construct the meta-toxic knowledge graph from initial toxic speech, it is essential to first identify the core toxic elements, i.e.",
    "entities and relations, within the speech.",
    "However, toxic semantics are often implicit and abstract, involving concepts such as race, gender and religion, rather than specific named entities."
  ]
}